<p>A point of clarification: The previous owners, if they were engaging in a polygamous lifestyle, were either in violation of the LDS Church&#8217;s tenants and in danger of excommunication, or (more likely) one of a multitude of splinter groups whose only claim to fame, if you can call it that, is practicing polygamy. They most assuredly are not Mormon. (nickname for the LDS Church) No worries though, as this happens all the time, the confusion of the actual Church and the offshoots, splinter groups, excommunicated groups. </p>
